    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think this would result in an infinite loop since the `next` pointer wouldn't advance.\n\nI haven't found any documentation on what `ALC10.alcGetString()` might return, but I guess the `next` pointer might also end up being null. Indeed, `Marshal.PtrToStrAnsi` only returns null when its argument is null, so the following would be a better fix:\n\n``` diff\ndiff --git a/OpenRA.Platforms.Default/OpenAlSoundEngine.cs b/OpenRA.Platforms.Default/OpenAlSoundEngine.cs\nindex 65f56f9..878be70 100644\n--- a/OpenRA.Platforms.Default/OpenAlSoundEngine.cs\n+++ b/OpenRA.Platforms.Default/OpenAlSoundEngine.cs\n@@ -56,14 +56,17 @@ static string[] QueryDevices(string label, int type)\n\n                        var devices = new List<string>();\n                        var next = ALC10.alcGetString(IntPtr.Zero, type);\n-                       do\n+                       if (next != IntPtr.Zero)\n                        {\n-                               var str = Marshal.PtrToStringAnsi(next);\n-                               next += str.Length + 1;\n-                               devices.Add(str);\n-                       } while (Marshal.ReadByte(next) != 0);\n+                               do\n+                               {\n+                                       var str = Marshal.PtrToStringAnsi(next);\n+                                       next += str.Length + 1;\n+                                       devices.Add(str);\n+                               } while (Marshal.ReadByte(next) != 0);\n+                       }\n\n-                       if (AL10.alGetError() != AL10.AL_NO_ERROR)\n+                       if (next == IntPtr.Zero || AL10.alGetError() != AL10.AL_NO_ERROR)\n                        {\n                                Log.Write(\"sound\", \"Failed to query OpenAL device list using {0}\", label);\n                                return new string[] { };\n```\n"
  },
