    "body": "@Mailaender Hi, I'm new here and I'm a fans of RA from China. Maybe I can do the translation work of Chinese.  \nBut now the code seems not working on my laptop.The OS is Fedora 23.\nAfter try to debug the code, I found if my language is Chinese, the code will not work. \n\n> next += str.Length + 1;\n\nI've change the code to this on my laptop.\n\n> next += System.Text.UnicodeEncoding.Default.GetByteCount(str) + 1; \n\nThis code will work. And of course the characters of Chinese is not right showed. Maybe we should do the multi-language support at a higher priority level ?\n"
  },
